    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect SL config request handling due to missing dedicated flag\n\n### Summary\nWhen calling `nr_ue_sl_phy_config_request()` the SL configuration was not being properly tracked because the function was incorrectly using the generic `received_config_request` flag instead of having its own dedicated flag. This caused SL processing logic to not recognize when SL configuration had been received, leading to unexpected behavior.\n\nThe fix adds a separate `received_sl_config_request` flag to properly track SL configuration requests.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/defs_nr_UE.h`: Added `bool received_sl_config_request` field to track SL config requests separately\n- `openair1/SCHED_NR_UE/fapi_nr_ue_l1.c`: Modified `nr_ue_sl_phy_config_request` to use the new SL-specific flag instead of the generic one\n- `openair1/PHY/INIT/nr_init_ue.c`: Added initialization of the new flag during UE initialization\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Call `nr_ue_sl_phy_config_request()` with a valid SL configuration\n2. Observe that SL processing logic that checks for configuration receipt does not properly detect the SL config\n3. This leads to SL procedures not being properly initialized or configured\n\nThe symptoms include SL transmission/reception not working as expected even after calling the configuration function.\n"
}